<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,292,496]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519">
Described from three localities in the north-south trending fold mountains of the Western Cape, and one locality (Nature’s Valley) in the Eastern Cape; not reported since the description. I can add the following locality, which extends the range of this species west, onto Table Mountain: 
<date box="[851,971,364,389]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="2010-09-24">
<number box="[851,878,364,389]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="24.0">24</number>
/ix/ 
<number box="[916,971,364,389]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Table Mountain National Park, Table Mountain, sandy stream in Echo Valley (
<figureCitation box="[761,829,399,424]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[229,1347,193,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[229,1347,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitats of Mesoceration species in South Africa. A) Western Cape, Matsikammaberg, permanent stream 1 km SE of Sewefontein farm— M. foggoi sp. nov., M. sewefonteinense sp. nov., M. umbrosum; B) Western Cape, False Bay, small stream on R 44 road below Boskloof Peak— M. sinclairi sp. nov., M. brevigranum; C) Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, permanent stream below Kangoberg on Gamkaskloof road— M. barriotum, M. littlekarroo, M. reticulatum, M. splendorum; D) Western Cape, Table Mountain National Park, Table Mountain, stream in Echo Valley— M. abstrictum, M. tabulare. Photos D. T. Bilton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243048/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number box="[816,829,399,424]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
D)—abundant. Note that the long distal lobe extends linearly from the apex of the main piece when dissected from fresh specimens, the curved appearance shown in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins" box="[381,822,471,496]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" refString="Perkins, P. D. &amp; Balfour-Browne, J. (1994) A contribution to the taxonomy of aquatic and humicolous beetles of the family Hydraenidae in southern Africa. Fieldiana Zoology, 77, 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1994" yearSuffix="p">
Perkins &amp; Balfour-Browne 
<number box="[689,745,472,496]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="1994.0">1994</number>
p. 
<number box="[779,822,472,496]" pageId="24" pageNumber="519" value="122.0">122</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) developing when the aedeagus is placed in lactic acid.
</paragraph>
